description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Medical Bank Dr, with a n&lt;span&gt;egotiated base on placement, knowledge, skills and experience. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JD: &lt;/strong&gt; Supplied once placement agreed &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Lincolnshire Partnership NHS Foundation Trust are looking to recruit caring, professional and suitably qualified Doctors to work across all grades and specialties on a bank basis ranging from a single shift to filling a substantive vacancy with evening, weekend and on-call shifts available. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Here at Lincolnshire Partnership NHS Foundation Trust we are keen to grow our existing team of Bank Doctors and are looking for Doctors on an ‘&lt;em&gt;as and when&lt;/em&gt;’ basis, across the following specialties:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adult Inpatient Mental Health Services (including Psychiatric Intensive Care Unit (PICU)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adult Community Mental Health Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CAMHS: inpatient and community&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Learning Disabilities: community&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Older Adult Mental Health Services: inpatient and community&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are looking for your next role in a friendly mental health setting or are seeking flexible work that fits around your other commitments, this could be a suitable option for you. In return for your hard work, commitment and reliability Lincolnshire Partnership NHS Foundation Trust offers a range of benefits to bank doctors, including:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competitive rates of pay as negotiated per placement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assistance with clinical appraisals and revalidation support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Long and short term placements, choice of available shifts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Holiday Pay rolled into hourly rate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access to the NHS Pension Scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of working on various wards and across specialties&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LPFT is an excellent award winning mental health and learning disability organisation and has the following accolades to show for its hard work and commitment to patient care:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rated as Good following CQC Inspection 2017 with CAMHS Service rated as Outstanding&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nationally recognised as one of the best mental health Trusts to work (HSJ Top 120 2015)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nationally recognised as the best place to train by our trainees within the East Midlands Region (Annual GMC survey 2015 &amp; 2016).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Awarded regionally/nationally for work on equality and diversity, patient safety and community partnerships.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Lincolnshire is steeped with history and brimming with life. Each year thousands of people choose to come to Lincolnshire, primarily for the quality of life it has to offer. There is a real mix of a thriving urban city, bustling historic market towns, idyllic villages, miles of unspoilt coastline and areas of natural beauty - a great place to live and work. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you would like to discuss the opportunities on offer in more detail, please complete the NHS Jobs application form which will be followed up through contact by the Medical Staffing Department.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
